I followed the examples in the test for the AI, and ended up getting errors when our game tried to save.  I looked into it a bit and to me, it appears to be something wrong with the JSON.toJson code.

I created a mock up and provided the output error information.

**To mock up the issue**:
1. Create a Person Class that implements Agent.
2. Add all unimplemented method stubs (update and onMessage)
3. Create a PersonState Enum that implements State<Person> 
4. Create unimplemented method stub onMessage for PersonState
5. Create a temporary ENUM "FRIST_ENUM", fill it with the overridden items (Enter, Update, Exit).
6. Add a StateMachine to Person class.
7. Instantiate the StateMachine with a DefaultStateMachine passing in the PersonState.FIRST_ENUM.
8. In another class, create a Person, then use Json.toJson(person) which causes the error.

